    <fr:title text="Bolza Problem">Bolza Problem</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
    Bolza problem is a fundamental formulation in the calculus of variations and optimal control that minimizes a cost functional consisting of both an integral term (running cost) and a terminal cost <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[J := \int _0^{t_f} L \big (x(t), u(t)\big ) dt + \Phi  \big (x(t_f)\big )]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is the running cost and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Phi ]]></fr:tex> is the terminal cost. The goal is to find the optimal control <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u(t)]]></fr:tex> that minimizes this cost functional subject to the system dynamics and boundary conditions.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
